message: If you use this work, please cite it using the metadata below.
type: dataset
title: Network Performance Measurement Experiment with Client, Server, and Proxy Components
abstract: This dataset documents a network performance measurement experiment involving
  client, server, and proxy components deployed across three nodes. The methodology
  involved configuring network interfaces and traffic shaping parameters to simulate
  controlled network conditions, followed by the execution of client and server applications
  under varying configurations. Energy consumption was recorded during each run, alongside
  packet data captured by the proxy. Results were visualized and archived using automated
  scripts, providing a comprehensive record of experimental setup and outcomes.
